1254B 101st Legislative Session 1254
2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1254
AMENDME NT 1254B
FOR THE HOUSE TAXATION ENGROSSED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Heinemann
1 An Act to exempt any soil amendment used exclusively for agricultural purposes
2 from sales tax, and to modify the definition of a soil amendment.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
4 Section 1. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 10-45:
5 There are specifically exempted from the provisions of this chapter and from the
6 computation of the amount of tax imposed by it, the gross receipts from the sale of any
7 soil amendment, as defined in § 38-19A-1, provided five hundred pounds or more of any
8 one of these products is sold in a single sale to be used exclusively for agricultural
9 purposes.
10 Section 2. That § 38-19A-1 be AMENDED:
11 38-19A-1. Terms as used in this chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, shall mean:
12 (1) "Brand," any trademark, product name, or other specific designation under which any
13 individual soil amendment is offered for sale;
14 (2) "Bulk," nonpackaged form;
15 (3) "Distributing," importing, consigning, manufacturing, producing, compounding, mixing or
16 blending any soil amendment, or offering for sale, selling, bartering, or otherwise supplying
17 any soil amendment in this state;
18 (4) "Distributor," any person who distributes any soil amendment in this state;
19 (5) "Investigational allowance," any allowance for variations inherent in the taking,
20 preparation and analysis of an official sample of a soil amendment;
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1254B 2 1254
1 (6) "Label," any display of all written, printed, or graphic matter upon the immediate container
2 or statement accompanying a soil amendment;
3 (7) "Labeling," any written, printed, or graphic matter, upon or accompanying any soil
4 amendment, or advertisements, brochures, posters, or television or radio announcements
5 used in promoting the sale of such soil amendment;
6 (7A) "Manipulated manure," any animal or vegetable manure collected or
7 stored in a manner consistent with practices commonly implemented in agricultural production
8 that has been subjected to practices including composting, mechanical dewatering, or
9 pelletizing or altered in any way to change chemical, physical, or biological characteristics;
10 (7B) "Microbe," any microbiological organism or mixture of microbiological
11 organisms intended to produce any physical, chemical, biochemical, biological, or other
12 change in the soil;
13 (8) "Minimum percentage," that percentage of soil amendment ingredient that shall be
14 present in a product before the product may be accepted for registration when distributed in
15 any form or manner;
16 (9) "Official sample," any sample of a soil amendment taken by the secretary and so
17 designated;
18 (10) "Percent," percentage by weight;
19 (11) "Registrant," any person who shall register any soil amendments under
20 the provisions of this chapter;
21 (12) "Secretary," the secretary of the Department of Agriculture and Natural
22 Resources of the State of South Dakota;
23 (13) "Soil amending ingredient," any substance which will improve the
24 physical, chemical, or other characteristic of the soil or improve crop production;
25 (14) "Soil amendment," any substance which is intended to improve the
26 physical, chemical, or other characteristics of the soil or improve crop production, except the
27 following: commercial fertilizer, unmanipulated animal manures, unmanipulated vegetable
28 manures, pesticides, lime or lime sludge produced by a water treatment facility, sewage
29 sludge, as defined in § 38-19-1, and compost as defined in § 38-19-1;
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

